GM Talking With Facebook Inc About Advertising Again-Reuters
Tuesday, 3 Jul 2012 04:38pm EDT
Reuters reported that General Motors Co and Facebook Inc are discussing the return of the U.S. automaker as a paid advertiser almost two months after GM said it would stop running ads on the social networking website. Although the two companies remain far from reaching an agreement, Facebook executives have assiduously courted the carmaker. One source said Facebook was not pushing for GM's immediate return, but offered to provide data showing the effectiveness of the website's paid ads.Â 
